name: tailwindcss
description: Use TailwindCSS for styling
glob: app/views/**/*.erb

---
When working with views and styling:

1. Use Tailwind CSS classes exclusively
- No custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- Follow the Tailwind CSS class naming conventions
- Use @apply in components only when necessary

2. Responsive Design
- Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)
- Mobile-first approach
- Test all breakpoints

3. Component Organization
- Use consistent class ordering
- Group related classes
- Extract common patterns into components
- Use Ruby helpers for repeated patterns

4. Dark Mode
- Support dark mode using dark: variant
- Test both light and dark modes

5. Accessibility
- Include proper ARIA attributes
- Ensure sufficient color contrast
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Follow a11y best practices 